### Module 1: Users & Authentication (`apps.users`)

Manages admin user accounts, login/logout with JWT, role-based permissions, account lockout, and audit logging.

| # | Function | Description | Input(s) | Output(s) | Roles |
|---|----------|-------------|----------|-----------|-------|
| 1.1 | **Login** (`POST /api/users/login/`) | Authenticate admin user, issue JWT tokens, record login audit | `username`, `password` | `access` token, `refresh` token, user profile + permissions dict | All admin roles |
| 1.2 | **Logout** (`POST /api/users/logout/`) | Record logout audit event | JWT token (header) | Success message | All authenticated admins |
| 1.3 | **Get Current User** (`GET /api/users/me/`) | Return profile and permissions of logged-in admin | JWT token (header) | User object with role, department, all permission flags | All authenticated admins |
| 1.4 | **List Admin Accounts** (`GET /api/users/admins/`) | List all active admin accounts sorted by role/department | JWT token (header) | Array of admin user objects | Super Admin only |
| 1.5 | **Create Admin Account** (`POST /api/users/admins/`) | Create a new admin user with role and department | `username`, `password`, `role`, `department`, optional `display_name`, `email`, `department_label` | New user `id` and `username` | Super Admin only |
| 1.6 | **Update Admin Account** (`PUT /api/users/admins/<pk>/`) | Update admin profile, role, department, or password | `pk` (URL), optional fields: `display_name`, `role`, `department`, `email`, `password` | Success message | Super Admin only |
| 1.7 | **Deactivate Admin** (`DELETE /api/users/admins/<pk>/`) | Soft-delete (deactivate) admin account. Cannot deactivate Super Admin. | `pk` (URL) | Success message | Super Admin only |
| 1.8 | **View Audit Log** (`GET /api/users/audit-log/`) | Retrieve admin activity audit trail (up to 300 entries) | Optional query params: `entity_type`, `action` | Array of audit log entries | Super Admin, Dean |
| 1.9 | **Account Lockout** (internal) | Lock account for 30 min after 5 failed login attempts | Failed login event | `locked_until` timestamp set | System (automatic) |
| 1.10 | **Record Audit Entry** (`write_audit()`) | Write a row to `AdminAuditLog` with action details and IP | `admin`, `action`, `entity_type`, `entity_id`, etc. | Database row created | System (internal) |

