### Module 4: Navigation & Pathfinding (`apps.navigation`)

Graph-based campus navigation with nodes and edges for path calculation.

| # | Function | Description | Input(s) | Output(s) | Roles |
|---|----------|-------------|----------|-----------|-------|
| 4.1 | **List Navigation Nodes** (`GET /api/navigation/nodes/`) | Get all non-deleted nodes (rooms, waypoints, entrances, etc.) | None (public) | Array of node objects with x, y, floor, type | All (read) |
| 4.2 | **Create Navigation Node** (`POST /api/navigation/nodes/`) | Add a navigable point on the campus graph | `name`, `node_type`, `facility`, `room`, `map_svg_id`, `x`, `y`, `floor` | New node object | Super Admin only |
| 4.3 | **Update Navigation Node** (`PUT /api/navigation/nodes/<pk>/`) | Modify node position or metadata | `pk` (URL) + updated fields | Updated node object | Super Admin only |
| 4.4 | **Delete Navigation Node** (`DELETE /api/navigation/nodes/<pk>/`) | Remove node from graph | `pk` (URL) | No content | Super Admin only |
| 4.5 | **List Navigation Edges** (`GET /api/navigation/edges/`) | Get all non-deleted edges connecting nodes | None (public) | Array of edge objects | All (read) |
| 4.6 | **Create Navigation Edge** (`POST /api/navigation/edges/`) | Connect two nodes with a weighted edge | `from_node`, `to_node`, `distance`, `is_bidirectional` | New edge object | Super Admin only |
| 4.7 | **Update Navigation Edge** (`PUT /api/navigation/edges/<pk>/`) | Modify edge properties | `pk` (URL) + updated fields | Updated edge object | Super Admin only |
| 4.8 | **Delete Navigation Edge** (`DELETE /api/navigation/edges/<pk>/`) | Remove edge from graph | `pk` (URL) | No content | Super Admin only |
| 4.9 | **Dijkstra Pathfinding** (frontend `pathfinder.js`) | Calculate shortest path between two nodes using Dijkstra's algorithm | `startId`, `endId`, nodes array, edges array | Path (node ID sequence) + total distance | Guest (client-side) |
| 4.10 | **GPS-to-Map Projection** (frontend `geolocation.js`) | Convert real GPS coordinates to SVG pixel coordinates | `lat`, `lng`, `mapBounds` | `{ x, y }` pixel position | Guest (client-side) |

